race.description: Kyneton Electrics Fillies & Mares Bm66 Handicap
race.comment: NEPRAVDA (1) is a leader who has raced in stronger metro company at her last two and there was only 1L in it at Morphettville last time. Will find this more to her liking and Stackhouse is reunited. In a top stable and is sure to go well. TORVEGA (5) is also free running and second-up scored an effortless 2.7L win over 1100m at Moe. Fitter again and won't have to improve much to threaten. DELICATE LADY (2) has an awkward barrier, but there was a lot to like about her Mornington placing last time. Always puts in, and she will sit off the speedsters and finish hard. BEDTIME ANGEL (3) led and won a 56 comfortably first-up and is still shy of her best. Draws low and will give a sight.
